citations:
    citation-acok-davos-iii:
        source: source-acok
        properties:
            locator: "Davos III"
            text_from_source: "Blackwater Bay was rough and choppy, whitecaps everywhere. Black Betha rode the flood tide, her sail cracking and snapping at each shift of wind. Wraith and Lady Marya sailed beside her, no more than twenty yards between their hulls. His sons could keep a line. Davos took pride in that."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Davos's POV of the Battle of the Blackwater. Fleet enters the river under Ser Imry Florent's command. The wildfire trap is sprung — hulks filled with wildfire ignite the Blackwater. Davos is blown into the river and swept toward the chain. His sons Matthos and Allard are present on Black Betha and Lady Marya respectively. Davos survives but his sons are killed."
